**Key Takeaways:**

1. AWS services are managed through a customer-owned AWS account.
2. Account linking enables VMware to cross-link SDDCs into a customer-owned AWS account.
3. Account linking is performed when the user executes a CloudFormation template within their AWS account.
4. The CloudFormation template creates roles which enable VMware to manage SDDC cross-linking.
5. The hosts within the SDDC are connected to the customer-owned VPC via cross-account ENIs.


